title: Vestal stays unbeaten, tops Seton in STAC semis
text:
Vestal stays unbeaten, tops Seton in STAC semis 
By wbng sports October 16, 2015 Updated Oct 16, 2015 at 6:35 PM EDT 
Endicott, NY (WBNG Binghamton) A second half goal off the foot of Rachel Wallace was the only score as Vestal beat Seton, 1-0, in the STAC girl's soccer semifinals. 
With the shutout win, Vestal still has not given up a goal this year. 
The Golden Bears move on to play the winner of Chenango Forks and Elmira in the STAC title game. 
The Blue Devils and Express play on Saturday at 2:30 p.m.
